1969 Nikki Jester attends first meeting of WWI and joins the MIA Chapter at
the Miami Springs Villas main building in a banquet room.
Dr. Sheffey from the Miami Children's Center was present and she gave a
presentation on the Chapter's Charity.
This building was the home of Glenn Hammond Curtiss, founder of Miami
Springs, Hialeah and Opa Lock, FL. The room mentioned as a banquet room was
originally Mr. Curtiss' garage.
